  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nI think the current error message in `_checkRole()` function is relatively expensive.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nHere is the current `checkRole()` function:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction _checkRole(bytes32 role, address account) internal view virtual {\r\n    if (!hasRole(role, account)) {\r\n        revert(\r\n            string(\r\n                abi.encodePacked(\r\n                    \"AccessControl: account \",\r\n                    Strings.toHexString(uint160(account), 20),\r\n                    \" is missing role \",\r\n                    Strings.toHexString(uint256(role), 32)\r\n                )\r\n            )\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhy are we giving an error like this? Isn't something like this better:\r\n\r\nDefine an error:\r\n```solidity\r\nerror MissingRole();\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd revert if the `account` has no `role`:\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction _checkRole(bytes32 role, address account) internal view virtual {\r\n    if (!hasRole(role, account)) revert MissingRole();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
